item.description:
arXiv:2505.16461v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: This work focuses on the nonhomogeneous nonlocal double phase problem \begin{align*}
  L_au(x)=f(x,u,D_s^p u, D_{a,t}^q u) \text{ in } \Omega, \end{align*} where $\Omega\subset\mathbb{R}^N$ is a bounded domain with Lipschitz boundary, $0<s,t<1<p\leq q<\infty$ with $tq\leq sp$ and the operator $L_a$ is defined as \begin{align*}
  L_a u(x)&=2\operatorname{P.V.}\int_{\mathbb{R}^N}|u(x)-u(y)|^{p-2}(u(x)-u(y))K_{s,p}(x,y)
  &\ \ \ +2\operatorname{P.V.}\int_{\mathbb{R}^N}a(x,y)|u(x)-u(y)|^{q-2}(u(x)-u(y))K_{t,q}(x,y)dy. \end{align*} We establish the equivalence between weak and viscosity solutions under boundedness and continuity assumptions. In addition, the local boundedness of weak solutions in some special cases on $f$ is also obtained using the notion of De Giorgi classes.
